</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6516C937FFBDF9EBFE0FFE1EF023" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B99369DC937FFBDF9EBFE0FFE1EF023" blockId="36.[151,1437,470,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDF9EBFE0FFE8BF3EB" bold="true" box="[151,274,470,497]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Corallum monopodial and pinnulate, unattached, with hook-like holdfast for support in soft sediments. Pinnules simple, bilateral and alternate. Spines simple, triangular, compressed. Polyps 
<quantity id="4CDE9B78C937FFBDFD1EFE22FB26F00C" box="[1122,1215,507,534]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“6 mm</quantity>
in transverse diameter (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B6CC937FFBDF9ACFDC6FEE2F023" author="Opresko, D. M." box="[208,379,543,569]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="411 - 442" refId="ref48859" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2002) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part II. Schizopathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen, 76, 411 - 442." type="journal article" year="2002">Opresko, 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6516C937FFBDF9BBFD9AFAE2F0D3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B99369DC937FFBDF9BBFD9AFAE2F0D3" blockId="36.[151,1437,470,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDF9BBFD9AFEA2F047" bold="true" box="[199,315,579,605]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D1EC937FFBDF8B9FD9AFD69F047" authority="Brook, 1889" authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[453,752,579,605]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Schizopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDF8B9FD9AFDCEF047" box="[453,599,579,605]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Schizopathes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B6CC937FFBDFB1DFD9AFD69F047" author="Brook, G." box="[609,752,579,605]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref46539" refString="Brook, G. (1889) Report on the Antipatharia collected by HMS Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Zoology, 32, 1." type="journal volume" year="1889">Brook, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one, within the order, to harbor species that do not depend on hard substrates for fixation, presenting a modified hook for support in soft bottoms (Wagner, 2015; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B6CC937FFBDF9EBFD52FEA6F0BF" author="Opresko, D. M." box="[151,319,651,677]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref48683" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1997) Review of the genus Schizopathes (Cnidaria: Antipatharia: Schizopathidae) with a description of a new species from the Indian Ocean. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 110 (2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="1997">Opresko, 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D1EC937FFBDFB05FD52FCBFF0BF" authorityName="Molodtsova &amp; Opresko" authorityYear="2017" box="[633,806,651,677]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Alternatipathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDFB05FD52FCBFF0BF" box="[633,806,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Alternatipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in particular, 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D1EC937FFBDFA8EFD55FB4FF0BC" authority="(Brook)" authorityName="Brook" baseAuthorityName="Brook" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1010,1238,651,678]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Alternatipathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="alternata">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDFA8EFD55FB9AF0BC" box="[1010,1027,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDFD6CFD52FBEEF0BF" box="[1040,1143,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">alternata</emphasis>
(Brook)
</taxonomicName>
are almost identical to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D1EC937FFBDF82EFD76FE7DF0D3" authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[338,484,687,713]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Schizopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDF82EFD76FE7DF0D3" box="[338,484,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Schizopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the exception that they have a basal holdfast for attaching to hard substrates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6516C937FFBDF9BBFD0BFD6BF0F7" box="[199,754,722,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B99369DC937FFBDF9BBFD0BFD6BF0F7" blockId="36.[151,1437,470,749]" box="[199,754,722,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B952EA8FC937FFBDF9BBFD0BFEF8F0F7" bold="true" box="[199,353,722,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
Cosmopolitan (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B6CC937FFBDFB6FFD0AFD7FF0F7" author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[531,742,723,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="3 - 7" refId="ref48147" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2014) Deep-sea fauna of European seas: An annotated species check-list of benthic invertebrates living deeper than 2000 m in the seas bordering Europe. Antipatharia. Invertebrate Zoology, 11, 3 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / invertzool. 11.1.02" type="journal article" year="2014">Molodtsova, 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
